</fr:meta>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>For any type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> we have a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="//erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {toProp}\,{A}]]></fr:tex> equipped with a unit map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\eta _{\mathsf {prop}}\colon  A \to \mathsf {toProp}\,{A}]]></fr:tex>; moreover, we have the following induction principle: for any family of <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001H.xml" title="Contractible type" addr="//erct/erct-001H" type="local">propositions</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B\colon  \mathsf {toProp}\,A \to  \mathsf {Prop}]]></fr:tex>, any function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b\colon  \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} B
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \eta _{\mathsf {prop}}\,x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex> extends to a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b^\sharp  \colon  \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x\colon \mathsf {toProp}\,A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x\colon \mathsf {toProp}\,A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x\colon \mathsf {toProp}\,A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x\colon \mathsf {toProp}\,A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} Bx]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
    <fr:p>When we have an element of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {toProp}\,A]]></fr:tex>, we will say that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is <fr:em><fr:strong>inhabited</fr:strong></fr:em>.</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
